The Lead Times, Africa and Western Ville University, San Diego, have conferred an award for transparency, selfless service and leadership on Nigeria’s Chief of Army Staff, Lt-Gen. Tukur Buratai. At the award ceremony in Accra, the COAS was hailed for selflessly leading the Nigerian army and tackling Boko Haram insurgency in the Lake Chad Basin region. The Commander of 81 Division, Maj-Gen Enobong Udoh received the award on Buratai’s behalf.